			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Thanks to everyone who&#8217;s entered or in the process of entering <a href="http://www.notebooks.com/2008/12/06/hp_magic_giveaway_enter/">Notebooks.com&#8217;s HP Magic Giveaway</a> contest. There are 20 ways for you to win on Notebooks.com, but unfortunately we&#8217;ll only have one winner. Luckily we&#8217;ve partnered with 49 other sites and each of them have a prize package to giveaway.</p>
<p>Some of the contests are super easy to enter and are random draws. Others will take more effort, but there&#8217;s less competition.</p>
<p>Here&#8217;s a list of some of contests you can enter today.</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://planetx64.com/">Planet 64</a></li>
<li><a href="http://absolutevista.com/">AbsoluteVista</a></li>
<li><a href="http://studentbloggers.org/">Student Bloggers</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.techiediva.com/">techiediva.com</a>/</li>
<li><a href="http://geek.com">geek.com</a></li>
<li><a href="http://techmamas.typepad.com/">Techmamas/</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.merlotmom.blogspot.com/">merlotmom</a></li>
<li><a href="http://noticiastech.com">noticiastech</a>/</li>
<li><a href="http://www.infowester.com/">Infowester.com</a>/</li>
<li><a href="http://GeeksToGo.com">Geeks To Go</a></li>
<li><a href="GearDiary.com">Gear Diary</a></li>
<li><a href="http://geeks.pirillo.com">Geeks!</a></li>
</ul>
<p>Chris Pirillo&#8217;s asking people to enter the contest by writing a how-to article on anything. I wrote an entry suggesting<a href="http://chris.pirillo.com/2008/12/09/five-geeky-ways-to-give-back-to-the-world-even-if-you%E2%80%99re-broke/"> Five Geeky Ways to Give Back to the World, Even if You’re Broke.</a> (no I&#8217;m not eligible to win), but all of you are. Head over to geeks.pirillo.com, write a how-to article and whoever gets the most comments wins the package. The contest ends tomorrow so hurry.<br />
<a href="http://techmamas.typepad.com/main/2008/12/hp-magic-giveaway-techmamas.html">Techmamas</a> is looking for a mom &#8220;Hero&#8221; that can put the prizes to good use. To enter all you need to do is leave a thoughtful comment and link to as many resources as possible to help tell your story. They&#8217;re asking that the package be shared with a school or charity.</p>
<p><a href="http://planetx64.com/">Planet64</a> is asking readers to build a slide show using Animoto. I haven&#8217;t tried that tool out yet, but I&#8217;m going to give it a shot since Carlos says it&#8217;s a good tool.</p>
<p>update: just created the below video using Animoto and liked what I saw. Super easy slideshow tool and there&#8217;s already some holiday music you can use to create your own videos.It will take some time for the videos to render though. There&#8217;s an export to YouTube option built into Animoto and the guys at Planet64 are great if you want to geek out about AMD processors or DSLRs.</p>
<p>If I had a bunch of free computers these are the folks I&#8217;d be sharing with:</p>
<p>[There is a video that cannot be displayed in this feed. <a href="http://www.notebooks.com/2008/12/09/dont-forget-to-enter-the-hp-magic-giveaway-more-sites/">Visit the blog entry to see the video.]</a></p>
<p>There&#8217;s only one more day to enter the <a href="http://geekstogo.com/">Geeks to Go </a>contest. All you need to do is leave a comment so this is an easy one to enter.</p>
<p><a href="http://geek.com">Geek.com</a> is holding a survey about netbooks and what kind of computer you plan on buying. There&#8217;s only three pages of buttons you need to click and it&#8217;s pretty painless.</p>
<p>I don&#8217;t read Spanish, but if you do you have an advantage to enter <a href="http://noticiastech.com/">Noricias Tech&#8217;s</a> give away.</p>
<p>TechieDiva wants to hear what you&#8217;d do with the prize if you won it and is holding a random drawing. You can be selfish, charitable or sell it on eBay. TechDiva won&#8217;t hold it against you, but they do want  to hear your real story.</p>


